participating-org.narrative:
The Perkumpulan Inisiatif (PI), is a non-governmental organization with membership-based organization. We have a vision as a National Center for Nations of Leadership. PI were stands with the goal of being a pioneering organization in advocacy and organizing people to realize power in favour to increasing the degree of life of marginalized groups.
To realize the goal, PI sets the main objective to be accomplishment;
1. Producing, reproducing and practicing a new knowledge to support the advocacy and organizing work through evidence based ;
2. Encourage adoption of policy making based the local knowledge and practices;
3. Encourages the participatory approaches in the implementation of public services to realization the pro-marginalized policy;
4. Strengthening the civil society capacity to promote their socio-economic, political, and cultural rights;
5. Engage actively strategic alliances than can magnify the impact of the change toward through good governance;
6. Encouraging individuals or group to have ability and courage to occupy strategic position within the power structure of the state.

Geographical coverage: PI was reside in West Java Province, who have 27 regency/cities, but in work coverage, PI are not limited to doing work in West Java only, but the entire territory of Indonesia, with the strategic partners that exist throughout the area of Indonesia.

Based on the vision, mission and the goals. PI was positioned itself as a #School of Taught#, which act as the supported organization for the civil society movement and marginalized groups, that combining research development with people organizing as part of the unique institution.
